text: Not a very fancy mall although the shops there trying to make them look fancy. They have a free toilet open to public on the ground floor, even if you are not a customer. So I have to leave a five star.
Great location. A better drop off point for those who have trouble getting about is in the carpark. Would be a lot better if you are coming here for your physiotherapy sessions!
I come here for my physiotherapy on level 3. They are very skillful. Building is also nice and clean, with a lift that makes it easy for us to go up to the physio.
there are some nice medical clinics and a lovely coffee shop on the ground floor. parking in the basement, very close to MRT

Cafe and retail shop at level 1. Mostly offices, gym or clinic from level 2 till 4. The carpark access (tight car clearance space) cater for 10-12 cars maximum excl. handicapped lot (depending on the car size). Need to drive with care into the carpark (B2).
